The paper deals with graph theory and specifically the chromatic number of $t$-perfect graphs. The paper also mentions $P_6$-free graphs as a potential area of investigation. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CO (Combinatorics).
